<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>NYT &gt; Technology</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/section/technology</link><description>Technology industry news, commentary, and analysis, with reporting on big tech, startups, and internet culture. The New York Times is a hub for conversation about news and ideas.</description><atom:link rel="self" href="https://rss.nytimes.com/services/xml/rss/nyt/Technology.xml" type="application/rss+xml" /><item><title>Peter G. Neumann, Who Warned of Computer Security Risks, Dies at 93</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/17/technology/peter-g-neumann-dead.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/17/technology/peter-g-neumann-dead.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/17/technology/peter-g-neumann-dead.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>For decades, he criticized the industry’s lax attitudes toward computer security and individual digital privacy. He also developed solutions.</description><dc:creator>John Markoff</dc:creator><pubDate>Sun, 17 May 2026 21:27:18 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Peter G Neumann</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computers and the Internet</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tech Industry</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computer security</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">DARPA</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">SRI International</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Obituary</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/05/24/multimedia/00neumann-kjbp-print1/00neumann-kjbp-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Jim Wilson/The New York Times</media:credit><media:description>Peter G. Neumann in 2012. At his death, he was still working full time on advanced computer security design being adopted by companies like Google and Microsoft.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>Google Appeals Landmark Ruling Declaring It a Monopolist in Search</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/22/technology/google-appeals-search-case.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/22/technology/google-appeals-search-case.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/22/technology/google-appeals-search-case.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>Google asked a federal appeals court on Friday to reverse a judge’s ruling that it had violated antitrust laws, as well as a requirement it share some data with rivals.</description><dc:creator>David McCabe</dc:creator><pubDate>Fri, 22 May 2026 16:34:58 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Google</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Competition law</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Search Engines</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computers and the Internet</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tech Industry</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Regulation and Deregulation</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Decisions and Verdicts</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Amit Mehta</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Federal Courts</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Justice Department</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/05/22/multimedia/22biz-google-hfo-qjbt/22biz-google-hfo-qjbt-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Kelsey McClellan for The New York Times</media:credit><media:description>The Google campus in Mountain View, Calif.</media:description></media:content></item></channel></rss>